  - Rationale: "Eastern corruption stealing Alberta's oil money"
  - Referendum: 2027-2028 (outcome uncertain, but 40-50% support = crisis)

**Economic Cost of Instability:**

**Productivity Loss:**
- Strikes: +300% (workers demand accountability, wage protection)
- Protests: Downtown cores shut down for weeks/months
- **Total productivity loss: $20-40 billion annually**

**Investment Freeze:**
- Companies halt ALL expansion plans (political risk too high)
- No new hiring, no new facilities, no R&D
- **Opportunity cost: $50-100 billion annually** (lost growth)

**Brain Drain:**
- Top talent emigrates: 100,000-200,000 annually
  - Doctors: 10,000/year (50% of annual production)
  - Engineers: 20,000/year
  - Tech workers: 30,000/year
  - Business executives: 10,000/year
  - Academics: 5,000/year
- **Lifetime economic value lost: $50-100 billion** (each skilled emigrant = $500,000-1M lifetime GDP contribution)

**5-Year Cumulative Impact:**
- **Social cost: $100-200 billion CAD** (protests, instability, productivity loss)
- **Political cost: INCALCULABLE** (potential breakup of Canada)
- **Permanent institutional damage:** Trust NEVER recovers (precedent: Italy 40 years post-Mafia, trust still <20%)
- **Generational trauma:** Millennials/Gen Z lose all faith in system (30-40% emigrate)

