  - U.S. gasoline prices: **+30-50%** ($3.50/gallon → $4.55-5.25/gallon)
  - Heating costs: **+40-60%** (natural gas shortage)
  - Electricity: Rolling blackouts (northern states)
  - **Consumer cost: $200-400 billion USD annually** (transportation, heating, electricity)

**MANUFACTURING INPUTS ($60B annually):**
- Aluminum, steel, auto parts, chemicals
