  - U.S. factory shutdowns: Integrated supply chains broken
  - Detroit auto plants: CLOSE (can't get Canadian parts)
  - **Manufacturing GDP: -$50-100 billion annually**

**BORDER CHAOS:**
- 400,000 trucks cross daily: 146 million/year
- Post-scandal delays: +2-4 hours per crossing (security concerns)
  - Precedent: 9/11 border slowdown cost **$8 billion/month** ($96B/year)
  - Precedent: COVID-19 disruptions cost **$300 billion over 18 months** ($200B/year)
- **U.S. cost: $50-100 billion USD annually** (supply chain delays, spoilage, just-in-time failure)

